# ProgressBar

> Finer-grained progress feedback with loading / success / error states.  
> **Status**: Beta


## Demo
### Stateful Progress
Loading, warning, and success in one panel.
:::TuffDemoWrapper{demo="ProgressBarStatefulProgressDemo" code-lang="vue"}
---
code: |
  <template>
    <TxProgressBar :percentage="32" show-text />
    <TxProgressBar :percentage="68" status="warning" show-text />
    <TxProgressBar success message="Done" />
    <TxProgressBar loading message="Syncing" />
  </template>
---
:::

### Dashboard Operations Progress
Multiple bars can represent release batches, quality checks, and capacity waterlines.
:::TuffDemoWrapper{demo="ComponentsOperationsStatusDemo" code-lang="vue" title="Operations status panel" description="Progress bars combine with metric cards and status badges to express dashboard health."}
---
code: |
  <template>
    <section class="grid gap-3">
      <TxProgressBar :percentage="86" status="success" height="10px" show-text flow-effect="shimmer" />
      <TxProgressBar :percentage="72" status="warning" height="10px" show-text flow-effect="wave" />
      <TxProgressBar :percentage="48" height="10px" show-text indicator-effect="sparkle" />
    </section>
  </template>
---
:::
## Basic Usage
::TuffCodeBlock{lang="vue"}
---
code: |
  <template>
    <TxProgressBar :percentage="45" show-text />
    <TxProgressBar loading />
  </template>
---
::

## API (Brief)
::TuffPropsTable
---
rows:
  - name: percentage
    type: 'number'
    default: '0'
    description: 'Progress percentage'
  - name: loading
    type: 'boolean'
    default: 'false'
    description: 'Indeterminate loading state'
  - name: status
    type: "'success' | 'error' | 'warning'"
    default: '-'
    description: 'Status tone'
  - name: message
    type: 'string'
    default: '-'
    description: 'Custom label'
  - name: showText
    type: 'boolean'
    default: 'false'
    description: 'Show percentage text'
  - name: maskVariant
    type: "'solid' | 'dashed' | 'plain'"
    default: 'solid'
    description: 'Track style'
  - name: flowEffect
    type: "'none' | 'shimmer' | 'wave' | 'particles'"
    default: 'none'
    description: 'Flow overlay effect'
  - name: height
    type: 'string'
    default: "'5px'"
    description: 'Bar height'
  - name: textPlacement
    type: "'inside' | 'outside'"
    default: 'inside'
    description: 'Text placement'
  - name: indicatorEffect
    type: "'none' | 'sparkle'"
    default: 'none'
    description: 'Endpoint indicator effect'
  - name: maskBackground
    type: "'blur' | 'glass' | 'mask'"
    default: 'blur'
    description: 'Track background style'
---
::

## Review Notes

- Source: `packages/tuffex/packages/components/src/progress-bar/src/TxProgressBar.vue`
- Recommendation: use `percentage` for known page-level progress; use `loading` or `indeterminate` for unknown-duration work instead of faking a percentage.
- Accessibility: the component renders `role="progressbar"`; `message` is used as both helper label and visible text.

